locality: Along right bank of Rio Calcoene, vic. Sete Ilhas

Comte River basin, Route N2, just N of the bridge over the Comte River, collected along the dirt track that runs to the E of N2 (near and along the trail to the Jesuit ruins). Upland and flooded tropical moist forest, partially disturbed.
L'Auberge des Orpailleurs at the bridge over the Orapu River on the Route de l'Est (highway N.2), ca. 33 km NW of Regina. On Orapu River to 200 m below L'Auberge des Orpailleurs.
Mataroni River. Base camp just above second rapids. Riverine forest 0-1 km upstream from camp.
Parque Nacional Mantanhas do Tumucumaque, Rio Anotaié. 1ª grande cachoeira.
Parque Nacional Montanhas do Tumucumaque, rio Anotaié. Primeira grande cachoeira. Rio Anotaié.
